Janu Botha of the Griquas during the Carling Currie Cup 2022 semifinal match between Bulls and Griquas at Loftus Versfeld Stadium.Â BackpagePix/Samuel Shivambu PRETORIA - The Bulls have been denied the chance of a unique double. While they will be in Saturday's URC final, their Currie Cup team fell in the semis. Griquas stormed Loftus on Friday. The visitors breached the Bulls' defence on three occasions in the second half. Those tries gave the Bulls too much to do to get back in the game. The hosts gave themselves hope when Bernard van der Linde pulled a try back. But all that was undone when a late penalty try secured the win for the Griquas. It ended 30 - 19 to the men from Kimberley. Griquas will face the Cheetahs or the Pumas in the final.